content:
Create and Send Enhanced Links in Messaging Sessions

To create and send enhanced links, you need to create a messaging component. This article applies to: 
Messaging for In-App, Messaging for Web, enhanced WhatsApp, enhanced Facebook Messenger, enhanced SMS, enhanced Apple Messages for Business, and Bring Your Own Channel.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience. View required editions

To create messaging components: 
Customize Application AND View Setup and Configuration or System Administrator

To send and receive messages in Messaging: Messaging Agent

Step 1: Create an Enhanced Link
Create your enhanced link on the Messaging Components page in Setup.
Click New Component, select Enhanced Link, enter your link text and URL, upload an image, and assign a name and description.

Step 2: Send an Enhanced Link in a Messaging Session
During an active messaging session, click the messaging component action, select the link you want to share, and click Insert. Click Send.
When sending an enhanced link component in an enhanced Facebook Messenger channel, agents see the link details, but customers see only the link title and URL or a link preview.

Note: Enhanced link components are available only in Text format in enhanced WhatsApp channels.
title: Creating and Sending Enhanced Links in Service Cloud Messaging
